\subsection*{Project synopsis}
\vspace{-2.8ex}

\begin{minipage}[t][2.2in]{0.65\textwidth}
    \vspace{0pt}

    You and your group members are mathematical consultants coordinating with
    several government agencies, including NASA, the Department of Energy, and
    the Department of Agriculture. You all have been tasked with the
    development of a model to help optimize the growth of algae cultures for
    human consumption in space habitats. Your group is aware that
    the aquaculture of algae is a highly refined science, but also
    appreciates the value of a good initial estimate, obtained without much
    expense. Indeed, your team will use the estimates it assembles to
    determine whether currently planned space habitats are capable
    of meeting the metabolic needs of their crews via algae aquaculture alone.
    Then, you will report your findings to the government bodies listed above.

